==Republication==
His novelette "[[The Merchant and the Alchemist's Gate]]" (2007) was also published in ''[[The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction]]''.

"The Great Silence", was included in ''[[The Best American Short Stories]]'' anthology for 2016, which is a rare honor for stories and authors that fall under the science fiction, fantasy, and horror genres.

==Works==
* "[[Tower of Babylon (story)|Tower of Babylon]]", ''[[Omni (magazine)|Omni]]'', 1990 ([[Nebula Award for Best Short Story|Nebula Award]] winner)
* "[[Division by Zero (story)|Division by Zero]]", ''Full Spectrum 3'', 1991 ([https://web.archive.org/web/20111121100139/http://www.fantasticmetropolis.com/i/division/full available online]) 
* "[[Understand (story)|Understand]]",  ''[[Asimov's Science Fiction]]'', 1991 ([https://web.archive.org/web/20140527121332/http://www.infinityplus.co.uk/stories/under.htm available online])
* "[[Story of Your Life]]", ''[[Starlight (anthology series)|Starlight 2]]'', 1998 ([[Nebula Award for Best Short Story|Nebula Award]], [[Theodore Sturgeon Award]] and [[Seiun Award]] winner)
* "The Evolution of Human Science" (also known as "Catching Crumbs from the Table"), ''[[Nature Magazine|Nature]]'', 2000 ([http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v405/n6786/full/405517a0.html available online]) 
* "Seventy-Two Letters",  ''Vanishing Acts'', 2000 ([[Sidewise Award for Alternate History|Sidewise Award]] winner) ([https://web.archive.org/web/20010802144026/http://www.tor.com/72ltrs.html available online])
* "[[Hell Is the Absence of God]]", ''[[Starlight (anthology series)|Starlight 3]]'', 2001 ([[Hugo Award for Best Novelette|Hugo Award]], [[Locus Award]], [[Nebula Award for Best Novelette|Nebula Award]] and [[Seiun Award]] winner)
* "Liking What You See: A Documentary", ''Stories of Your Life and Others'', 2002
* "What's Expected of Us",  ''[[Nature Magazine|Nature]]'', 2005 ([http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v436/n7047/full/436150a.html available online])
* "[[The Merchant and the Alchemist's Gate]]",  [[Subterranean Press]], 2007 and ''[[The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction|F&SF]]'', September 2007 ([[Nebula Award for Best Novelette|Nebula Award]], [[Hugo Award for Best Novelette|Hugo Award]] and [[Seiun Award]] winner ([https://web.archive.org/web/20080214145811/http://www.sfsite.com/fsf/fiction/tc01.htm available online])
* "[[Exhalation (short story)|Exhalation]]",  ''Eclipse 2'', 2008 (BSFA, [[Locus Award]], and [[Hugo Award for Best Short Story|Hugo Award]] winner) ([http://www.lightspeedmagazine.com/fiction/exhalation/ available online]) 
* "[[The Lifecycle of Software Objects]]",  [[Subterranean Press]], July 2010 ([[Locus Award]], [[Hugo Award for Best Novella|Hugo Award]] and [[Seiun Award]] winner) ([http://subterraneanpress.com/magazine/fall_2010/fiction_the_lifecycle_of_software_objects_by_ted_chiang available online])
* "Dacey's Patent Automatic Nanny", ''The Thackery T. Lambshead Cabinet of Curiosities'' (edited by [[Jeff VanderMeer]] and [[Ann VanderMeer]]) June 2011
* "[[The Truth of Fact, the Truth of Feeling]]", [[Subterranean Press]] Magazine, August 2013 ([https://subterraneanpress.com/magazine/fall_2013/the_truth_of_fact_the_truth_of_feeling_by_ted_chiang available online])
* "The Great Silence", [[E-flux publications|e-flux Journal]], May 2015 (Included in ''[[The Best American Short Stories]]'', 2016) ([http://supercommunity.e-flux.com/texts/the-great-silence/ available online])

===Collections===
* ''[[Stories of Your Life and Others]]'' ([[Tor Books|Tor]], 2002) ([[Locus Award]] for Best Collection), republished as ''Arrival'' ([[Picador (imprint)|Picador]], 2016)

===Film===
A film adaptation by [[Eric Heisserer]] of "Story of Your Life", titled ''[[Arrival (film)|Arrival]]'' and directed by [[Denis Villeneuve]], was released in 2016 to a critical and commercial success. It stars [[Amy Adams]] and [[Jeremy Renner]].<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jeremy-renner-joins-amy-adams-779876| title=Jeremy Renner Joins Amy Adams in Sci-Fi 'Story of Your Life'| publisher=The Hollywood Reporter | date=6 March 2015}}</ref>''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Zutter|first1=Natalie|title=Your First Look at ''Arrival'', the Adaptation of Ted Chiang’s Novella ''Story of Your Life''|url=http://www.tor.com/2016/08/08/first-look-arrival-amy-adams-jeremy-renner-ted-chiang/|website=TOR|publisher=[[tor.com]]|accessdate=17 August 2016|date=August 8, 2016}}</ref>

==Teaching==
Chiang was an [[List of Clarion Writers Workshop Instructors |instructor]] at the [[Clarion Workshop |Clarion Science Fiction and Fantasy Writers' Workshop]] at UC San Diego in 2012 and 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://clarion.ucsd.edu/graduates.html |title = Clarion at UC San Diego Graduates and Instructors |website= Clarion |accessdate = December 9, 2016 }}</ref>
